In England, in the seven days to 20 February, there were 234,902 new confirmed cases (415.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 13 February, there were 305,049 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 23% (70,147 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 25 February is 15,998,983 (28,291.7 cases per 100,000 population).
